{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 01:47:58.199376", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nExecutive Summary\n- Overall data-plane connectivity between hosts is currently functional, but the control plane has a critical anomaly: one spine (spine_router_0_1) has no established BGP sessions due to an AS number misconfiguration.\n- Impact: Loss of path redundancy/ECMP through this spine. Traffic is currently flowing via alternate spines (e.g., spine_router_0_0), so reachability appears fine, but the fabric is degraded and operating with reduced resiliency.\n\nObserved Symptoms and Tests\n- End-to-end reachability:\n  - pc_0_0 ↔ pc_0_1: Ping successful, 0% loss, RTT ~2–3 ms.\n  - Bulk reachability tests across many hosts showed 0% packet loss and low RTTs, indicating data-plane is operational via remaining paths.\n- BGP status (key findings):\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200):\n    - One neighbor down: 172.16.1.16 (AS 65101) in Active state.\n    - Other neighbors established; receiving 31 prefixes from each.\n    - Routing table shows full set of 10.x/24 routes via other spines.\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201):\n    - One neighbor down: 172.16.1.18 (AS 65101) in Active state.\n    - Other neighbors established; receiving 31 prefixes from each.\n  - spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100):\n    - All BGP sessions established with super-spine (65000) and leaves (AS 65200–65207).\n    - Receiving prefixes as expected (e.g., PfxRcd from leaves: 4/leaf in this sample).\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000):\n    - Most spine peers established except neighbor 172.16.0.3 (expected AS 65101) is in Active state.\n  - spine_router_0_1:\n    - Local AS configured as 65701 (unexpected).\n    - All 12 BGP neighbors are Idle/never up (both to super-spine and to leaves).\n    - Routing table has only connected routes; no learned BGP routes.\n\nFault Localization\n- Faulty device: spine_router_0_1.\n- Affected adjacencies:\n  - To super_spine_router_0 over 172.16.0.2/31 and related interfaces: BGP never established.\n  - To leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1 over 172.16.1.16/31 and 172.16.1.18/31: BGP in Active on leaves; Idle on spine.\n\nRoot Cause\n- Misconfigured BGP local AS on spine_router_0_1:\n  - Observed: router bgp 65701 and BGP summary shows local AS 65701.\n  - Expected: 65101 (consistent with:\n    - super_spine_router_0’s neighbor config for 172.16.0.3 showing AS 65101 and Active state;\n    - leaf routers’ neighbor configs expecting AS 65101 on 172.16.1.16 and 172.16.1.18).\n- The AS mismatch prevents EBGP session establishment with all its neighbors.\n\nEvidence (highlights)\n- spine_router_0_1:\n  - “router bgp 65701” in running config.\n  - BGP summary: all neighbors Idle, RIB empty.\n- super_spine_router_0:\n  - Neighbor 172.16.0.3 AS 65101 in Active state (configured expectation), indicating mismatch with peer’s actual AS.\n- leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1:\n  - Neighbors 172.16.1.16/18 (AS 65101) in Active, while other spine neighbors are Established.\n- spine_router_0_0:\n  - Normal BGP operation with super-spine and leaves, confirming the rest of the control plane is healthy.\n\nImpact Assessment\n- Current reachability: OK due to alternate spines (e.g., spine_router_0_0) carrying traffic.\n- Degraded state: Loss of ECMP and redundancy via spine_router_0_1; potential for suboptimal load distribution and a single point of failure if remaining spines/links experience issues.\n\nConclusion\n- Anomaly detected: Yes.\n- Localization: spine_router_0_1.\n- Root cause: Incorrect BGP local AS configured (65701 instead of the expected 65101), causing all EBGP sessions on that spine to remain down.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 21379, "output_tokens": 3221, "total_tokens": 24600, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 20992}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2240}}}
